text: Czadrów () is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Kamienna Góra, within Kamienna Góra County, Lower Silesian Voivodeship, in south-western Poland. It lies approximately south of Kamienna Góra, and south-west of the regional capital Wrocław. The village has a population of 720. ==References== Category:Villages in Kamienna Góra County
title: Czadrów
